post_text: September is Suicide Awareness Month. The Lubbock Out of the Darkness Walk provides an opportunity for community members to encourage, support, and remember those who have been affected by suicide. This year's Walk out of the Darkness will be a virtual event. SHS's Social Action and STUCO invite you to participate by walking at the track at 7:30 AM on Friday, September 11th. We would like to have a record of your attendance and distance walked so that our miles walked together can be counted in the Walk Out of the Darkness Lubbock Experience.

post_text:
GAME DAY PARADE!!
Tomorrow’s pep rally will be an outdoor parade around all SISD campuses. The parade will include band, football, and cheerleader members marching down the center of the street starting at the elementary school and ending at the middle school. We ask that parents watch the parade and support the kids from across the street of the school. All SISD students not involved in the parade will observe and support the parade members while standing on school property and not across the street of the school.

There will be a short video made available to the general public after 1pm tomorrow. The video will include a cheer by the cheerleaders, an introduction of each player, and a talk by Coach Cummings. The link will be shared online. Go Roughnecks!!

post_text: High school students...I know this is not the way any of you envisioned this school year going. It isn’t close to what we envisioned either as a staff. So much of this is out of your control and ours. Let’s make the best of our current situation! Your parents, teachers, coaches, and sponsors have all been preparing you for life’s challenges and now it is your turn to do what you always do...take on new challenges and overcome! Good luck! You all are the best! Make the best of this situation and give your Sundown all!

Teacher Parade TODAY!

Today at 5:30 our teachers will be following the route below to wave and say hello! We are so very excited! We want to see everyone while keeping our social distancing practices and safety intact. post_text:
POST-SEASON BASKETBALL HONORS FOR BOYS:
Please help congratulate these young men on a memorable basketball season!

FROM COACH IGO:
I want to Thank You and let you guys know how incredibly grateful we are to have Roughneck Nation show your support and love and appreciation for these student athletes during this incredible basketball season this year! These young men had an outstanding run this year and accomplished so much, but more importantly learned to love the journey and process, play together as a brotherhood, and battle and compete. Just wanted to share a few of the All-District Honors now that the season has ended.

District 5 2-A

Defensive MVP - Gus Davis

All-District Selections - Brice Legan, Michael Ojeda, Carson Holson

Defensive All-District - Omar Lopez

Honorable Mention All-District - Carson Boggs

Academic All-District - Brandon Kenley, Carson Boggs, Jon Torrez, Omar Lopez, Brice Legan, Gus Davis, Carson Holson, Karli Torrez

Congrats Roughnecks!

POST-SEASON BASKETBALL HONORS FOR GIRLS: Please help in congratulating the following young ladies on and incredible season.

FROM COACH LEGAN:
We were able to win our 5th consecutive district championship as well as winning the bi-district championship. Our girls really worked hard and got better as the season progressed. The following young ladies have earned postseason awards.

TABC Region 1-2A All Region Team
Mckenzie Lee

District 5-2A Defensive MVP
Geneva Cortez

Mckenzie Lee
Lexie Lee
Emily Rodriguez

Natalie Urias

Alyzah McGlasson

Academic All District
Grace McAdams
Geneva Cortez
Alyzah McGlasson
Emily Rodriguez
Alex De La Cerda
Mckenzie Lee
Lexie Lee
Jonna Pool
Karli Torrez
Shea Beadles

The girls finished the year 19-16 with a district and bi-district championship.
Our girls also finished the season with a cumulative 92.52 team GPA. Congrats Roughettes!

FROM COACH NEWTON:
I am very excited to announce the following young men have qualified to compete at the Regional Powerlifting meet that will be here in Sundown next Saturday, March 14th. These kids had to finish in the top 12 in their respective weight classes to qualify. Our region is massive and has over 80 schools who compete in powerlifting, so this is quite a feat. This is by far the largest group I have had advance since I have been here, so I am extremely proud of this group of kids. Lots of hard work and effort has gone into this group as well as all of our kids who competed this season. I am looking forward to seeing us compete next week and hopefully you can catch them as well. The regional qualifiers are as follows:

132 Class Aidon Olivas
132 Class Carlos Perez
148 Class Pablo Mendoza
165 Class Cade Conway
181 Class Blake Hulse
181 Class EJ Hernandez
181 Class Kevin Garcia
198 Class Jonathan Golightly
198 Class Gavin Richardson
198 Class Diego Hernandez
220 Class Zakary Gragson
242 Class Andy Castillo
SHW Class Nico Rodriguez

In addition to the bake sale today that lasts until 2pm, we are also selling t-shirts in honor of LaDonna Fryar. These order forms will be at the bake sale tomorrow or if you’d like to print one off and bring it with you, that’s fine too!
The sunflower is the official symbol of hope for those battling ALS AND ALS is also represented by the colors red and blue...so we chose the beautiful royal blue and Daniel did a wonderful job coming up with this design!
The due date is not until February 20th. Message Sarah Goodman or Angela Greenhaw if you have questions.
Thanks for your support!

post_text: The SHS Cheerleaders recognized CHD Awareness week at the basketball games on Friday night. Pictured is 5th grader Kolt McDaniel with the SHS Cheerleaders as well as the Roughette & Roughneck Basketball teams. Kolt energized the crowd and brought them to their feet! We would also like to recognize Haley Jeffcoat from SES. The SHS Cheerleaders wanted to also honor the Griffith family and their daughter Reese's memory. They would like for everyone to #LoveLikeReese. February 7th-14th is Congenital Heart Defect Awareness week and the stands were packed with RED. Thank you SHS Cheerleaders for honoring our CHD kids and families!
